<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Kollins</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-16 09:01:17</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Both Choon and Froon are in WEST Karana.<BR>
Broon is a pushover and Droon is just mean but those two either don't drop runes or their runes won't work for lambent quests.<BR>
Do like I did and grow some lambent kahunas; I solod both of them and obtained both runes at level 27 (both conned red).<BR>
Level 14 song distingushes the two runes so don't worry about getting them mixed up before you get a chance to hit solusek.<BR>
Have selo's, charm, bellow's memmed along with your battle songs especially psalm of warmth or cold and don't bring a friend unless they are a lot higher than 27 or like dying as this bard trick works best solo (:<BR>
Hit WK from NK on the trail, you will come to a house that is in a valley where the hill has a stone pillar on it (right behind Cheif Goonda's spot).<BR>
Run up on selo's, with drum, target Choon and aggro both then run back down past the house and into the open grass.<BR>
Charm Choon sick him on Froon, keep selo's UP, re charm as needed and keep your distance!<BR>
Once Froon drops Choon will still have a few hitpoints, he is a pain to tank down even this low on health so my advice is small circles, 2 beats bellows, one beat selo's, until he falls.<BR>
You may be able to tank down the last bit of health but when I tried the only reason he fell was because he was REALLY low on health and I had fire shield up.<BR>
Now you have half the quest for vambraces and boots done, go hit solusekbut be warned the mage and champ are not as easy.<BR>
Kollins Kahunas, Woodelf Bard of Bertoxxulous<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
