<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Doktoor Roksteady</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-19 19:59:36</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I kill Froon and Choon in WK quite often for exp. They actually will kill eachother about fifty percent of the time, so what you do is watch they're health as it gets low, then snare the one that is closest to dying if it's a dead heat. This slows the eventual loser down 30 percent so you can assure his death. Once he's dead, you charm the one away from the corpse and hit hotkeyed /pet sit down. he'll stay where you leave him and you can loot in peace. After charm wears off, just use the bellow and selos to finish him off. Good exp and both runes. Make sure you use the right one when you hand em in though. <BR>
<BR>
BTW...1. they drop the rune about 75 percent of the time.<BR>
      2. the spawn rate is 20 minutes on both of them.<BR>
      3. loc of spawn is like -8000 -1200.<BR>
      4. PULL EM SOUTH AWAY FROM THE OGRES!<BR>
      5. they spawn on top of a hill by a totem.<BR>
<BR>
Hope this helps out those of the fellow best class in Norrath!<BR>
<BR>
Doktoor Roksteady bard of 30 songs working for peace on Vallon.<BR>
<BR>
P.S. Lose the buckets on your heads and have some style bards!</font></td></tr></table>
